The paper proposes a saliency detection model using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and focuses on computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses weakly supervised learning and combines forward and backward features, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and feature selection, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
